# Tailwind CSS and Styling Conventions

## Design System Colors
Based on [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts):

### CSS Variables
The project uses CSS variables for theming:
- `--primary` and `--primary-foreground`
- `--secondary` and `--secondary-foreground`  
- `--muted` and `--muted-foreground`
- `--border`, `--input`, `--ring`

### Standard Color Usage
- **Primary Blue**: `text-blue-600`, `bg-blue-50`, `hover:text-blue-700`
- **Gray Scales**: `bg-gray-100`, `text-gray-700`, `border-gray-200`
- **Background**: `bg-white` for cards, `bg-gray-100` for page background

## Layout Patterns

### Page Layout (from [app/layout.tsx](mdc:app/layout.tsx)):
```tsx
<div className="min-h-screen flex">
  <aside className="w-60 bg-white border-r border-gray-200 flex flex-col py-8 px-4 shadow-sm">
    {/* Sidebar */}
  </aside>
  <main className="flex-1 p-8">
    {/* Page content */}
  </main>
</div>
```

### Navigation Links:
```tsx
<Link className="flex items-center gap-3 px-3 py-2 rounded-lg text-gray-700 hover:bg-blue-50 hover:text-blue-700 transition font-medium">
  <Icon className="text-xl" />
  Link Text
</Link>
```

## Component Styling Patterns

### Form Styling:
- Form containers: `space-y-4` for vertical spacing
- Input groups: Wrap in `<div>` with label + input
- Buttons: Use UI button component with variants

### Card/Container Styling:
- Cards: `bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg shadow-sm`
- Padding: `p-4` for small, `p-6` for medium, `p-8` for large
- Spacing: `space-y-4` between sections, `gap-4` for flex layouts

### Typography:
- Headings: `text-2xl font-bold` for main titles
- Labels: `font-medium` for form labels
- Body: Default styling, use `text-gray-700` for secondary text

## Responsive Design
- Use responsive prefixes: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`, `2xl:`
- Mobile-first approach
- Container max-width: `2xl:max-w-[1400px]`

## Animation and Transitions
- Use `transition` class for hover effects
- Available animations: `accordion-down`, `accordion-up`
- Keep animations subtle and fast (0.2s ease-out)

## Custom Utilities
The project includes:
- `tailwindcss-animate` plugin for animations
- Custom border radius using CSS variables
- Extended font family stack with system fonts